{"lemma": "قُفّاز", "slug": "قُفّاز", "root": "ق.ف.ز", "root_slug": "ق-ف-ز", "root_link": "/words/roots/ق-ف-ز", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n36044", "n36045"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8F%D9%81%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%B2"}}, "translations": {"en": "glove", "fa": "دستکش", "ur": "دستانہ", "tr": "eldiven", "id": "sarung tangan", "bn": "দস্তানা", "es": "guante", "fr": "gant", "de": "Handschuh", "ru": "перчатка", "zh": "手套"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of قَفَزَ (qafaza) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "glove", "examples": [{"text": "وَالْوَرْدُ يُنَقَّى فِي شَهْرِ أُكْتُوبِرَ مِنَ الْعُشْبِ بِالْأَيَادِي بِالْقُفَّازَاتِ", "english": "Roses are cleansed of weeds in October with gloved hands."}]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Transfixed from a rare variant قَفَز (qafaz) of قَفَص (qafaṣ, “cage”), because the surface of a crudely structured glove will often resemble a grid, even in feeling if a medieval gauntlet of iron."}, "ipa": ["/qu.faːz/", "/quf.faːz/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n36044", "headword_ar": "قَفَّازٌ", "root": "qfz", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That leaps, jumps, springs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bounds, much,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "often;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, * Msb;) [and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qafuwzN", "text_ar": "قَفُوزٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", occurring in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rfA^", "text_ar": "رفا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the M and K, applied as an epithet to a gazelle.] ―         -b2-  Hence,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaf~aAzapN", "text_ar": "قَفَّازَةٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A female slave:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because she seldom remains still. You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaA A@bona Alqaf~aAzapi", "text_ar": "يَا ا@بْنَ القَفَّازَةِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "O son of the female slave."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A.)"}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n36045", "headword_ar": "قُفَّازٌ", "root": "qfz", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A kind of glove; a thing which is made for the two hands,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hands and arms, stuffed with cotton,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, L, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and having buttons which are buttoned upon the fore arms,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, L,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "worn by a woman as a protection from the cold;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, L, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "they are made of skins,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of felt; are worn by the women of the Arabs of the desert; and extend to the bones of the elbow:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, TA:) a pair of them is called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "quf~aAzaAni", "text_ar": "قُفَّازَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, L:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing which the women of the Arabs of the desert make for themselves, stuffed with cotton, covering a woman's two hands, with her fingers, and,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "some add,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having buttons upon the fore arm; like what the carrier of the falcon wears:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing which those women make for themselves, covering the fingers and hand and arm:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing which the sportsman"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the falconer"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wears upon each hand,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hand and arm, of skin,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of felt,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wool:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a kind of women's ornament for the hands and feet,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the hands and arms and the feet and legs:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a reticulated iron thing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HadiydapN mu$ab~akapN", "text_ar": "حَدِيدَةٌ مُشَبَّكَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", accord. to the TA, as from the K, but in the CK"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mu$otabikapN", "text_ar": "مُشْتَبِكَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon which the falcon sits."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b2-  And [hence,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Whiteness in the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$aAEir", "text_ar": "اَشَاعِر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hairs next the hoof"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of a horse."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K. [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qafiza", "text_ar": "قَفِزَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "quf~aza", "text_ar": "قُفَّزَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aqofazu", "text_ar": "اَقْفَزُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".])"}], "source_refs": ["S", "L", "K", "TA", "Msb", "Mgh"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}